comment.body:
You can inject it like this:

```
       .UseEntityFrameworkPersistence(ef =>
       {
           ef.UseSqlServer(configuration.GetConnectionString("Workflow-DB")!);
       }, true))
```
       
&& for Quartz
       
```
          .AddQuartzTemporalActivities(configureQuartz: quartz => quartz.UsePersistentStore(store =>
        {
            store.UseJsonSerializer();
            store.UseSqlServer(providerOptions =>
            {
                providerOptions.ConnectionString = configuration.GetConnectionString("Workflow-DB") ?? string.Empty;
                providerOptions.ConnectionStringName = "Workflow-DB";
            }, "Workflow-DB");
            store.UseClustering();
        }))
```

@sfmskywalker  Well, either it's currently still broken, or my setup is wrong, which is also very possible.

As far as I know, we need to use `UseWorkflowRuntime` to activate the Journal, right?

For SQLite the following seems to work:
```csharp
    elsa.UseWorkflowManagement(management => management.UseEntityFrameworkCore(m => m.UseSqlite()));
    elsa.UseWorkflowRuntime(runtime =>
    {
        runtime.UseEntityFrameworkCore(ef => ef.UseSqlite());
    });
```

So for Postgres I would expect something like this:

```csharp
    elsa.UseWorkflowManagement(management => management.UseEntityFrameworkCore(m => m.UsePostgreSql("...")));
    elsa.UseWorkflowRuntime(runtime =>
    {
        runtime.UseEntityFrameworkCore(ef => **ef.UsePostgresSql("...)**); // UsePostgresSql does not exist here!
    });
```

While `UseSqlite` for WorkflowRuntime exists, `UsePostgresSql` does not. Is a different setup needed?

I've installed packages for EFCore, Postgres as well as Sqlite
```csharp
    <PackageReference Include="Elsa.EntityFrameworkCore" Version="3.0.0-preview-preview-3.0.0-740-hotfix-1.771" />
    <PackageReference Include="Elsa.EntityFrameworkCore.PostgreSql" Version="3.0.0-preview-preview-3.0.0-740-hotfix-1.771" />
    <PackageReference Include="Elsa.EntityFrameworkCore.Sqlite" Version="3.0.0-preview-preview-3.0.0-740-hotfix-1.771" />
```
